      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW XENA (8) is a fast beginner who has shown good improvement at her last two starts, the latest scoring at Shepparton over 450m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Great chance to get the job done again. DADDY COOL (1) is a talented dog who is a winner of 16 races and filled a minor placing latest when second at Warragul (22.88). Form here at this distance is sound. Can measure up. GROUND CONTROL (5) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.3 lengths at this track in a handy 24.29 beating Cash The Lot. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Looks a key chance if runs up to latest figure. HOLLY ROSE (2) scored last time and appeals as a top-three prospect.",
